.TH MACHINESTATE 1 "December 2025" "machinestate 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
machinestate \- system state reporter for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B machinestate
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B machinestate
is a fast, single-binary system health reporter that collects comprehensive
system metrics, detects issues, and outputs reports in multiple formats.
.PP
It monitors CPU, memory, disk, network, packages, services, security,
hardware, Docker containers, Snap packages, GPUs, and system logs.
Issues are automatically detected with severity levels and fix recommendations.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-format =\fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: terminal (default), html, json, markdown, all
.TP
.BR \-\-output =\fIPATH\fR
Output file path (default: stdout)
.TP
.BR \-\-stream
Enable continuous streaming mode (JSONL output)
.TP
.BR \-\-interval =\fISECONDS\fR
Interval between streaming cycles in seconds (default: 5)
.TP
.BR \-\-duration =\fISECONDS\fR
Maximum streaming duration in seconds (0 = infinite)
.TP
.BR \-\-count =\fIN\fR
Number of streaming cycles (0 = infinite)
.TP
.BR \-\-collectors =\fILIST\fR
Comma-separated collectors to stream (default: all)
.TP
.BR \-\-http =\fIPORT\fR
Run HTTP server on specified port (e.g., 8080)
.TP
.BR \-\-mcp
Run as MCP server (stdio transport for Claude Code integration)
.TP
.BR \-\-config =\fIPATH\fR
Path to YAML config file (default: ~/.config/machinestate/config.yaml)
.TP
.BR \-\-quiet
Suppress terminal output when using \-\-format all
.TP
.BR \-\-json\-compact
Output minified JSON (single line)
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version and exit
.SH COLLECTORS
The following collectors gather system information:
.TP
.B os
Operating system name, version, kernel, architecture
.TP
.B system
CPU usage, memory, swap, load average, uptime, timezone
.TP
.B disk
Filesystem usage, free space, inode status
.TP
.B network
Network interfaces, IP addresses, listening ports, connectivity
.TP
.B packages
APT updates, security updates, broken and held packages
.TP
.B services
Systemd failed units, zombie processes, top CPU/memory processes
.TP
.B security
Firewall status (UFW), SSH status, failed login attempts (24h)
.TP
.B hardware
Battery health and capacity, temperature sensors, crash reports
.TP
.B docker
Docker containers (running/stopped), images, disk usage
.TP
.B snaps
Snap packages, disk usage, pending refreshes
.TP
.B gpu
GPU temperature, utilization, memory (NVIDIA, AMD, Intel)
.TP
.B logs
Log analysis: errors, warnings, OOM events, kernel panics (24h)
.SH HTTP ENDPOINTS
When running with \fB\-\-http\fR, the following REST API endpoints are available:
.TP
.B /health
Health check endpoint (returns {"status":"ok"})
.TP
.B /api/report
Full system report as JSON
.TP
.B /api/issues
Detected issues (optional query: ?severity=critical|warning|info)
.TP
.B /api/system
CPU, memory, load average, uptime
.TP
.B /api/disk
Filesystem usage (optional query: ?mount=/)
.TP
.B /api/network
Network interfaces and listening ports
.TP
.B /api/packages
APT package status
.TP
.B /api/services
Systemd services and top processes
.TP
.B /api/security
Firewall and SSH status
.TP
.B /api/hardware
Battery and temperature information
.TP
.B /api/docker
Docker containers and images
.TP
.B /api/snaps
Snap packages
.TP
.B /api/gpu
GPU information
.TP
.B /api/logs
Log analysis
.TP
.B /api/config
Current configuration thresholds
.TP
.B /metrics
Prometheus format metrics
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration thresholds can be set in a YAML file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
# ~/.config/machinestate/config.yaml
disk_warning_percent: 80
disk_critical_percent: 90
memory_warning_percent: 90
battery_health_warning: 80
battery_health_critical: 50
uptime_warning_days: 30
gpu_temp_warning: 80
gpu_temp_critical: 90
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/machinestate/config.yaml
User configuration file
.TP
.I /etc/machinestate/config.yaml
System-wide configuration file
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate terminal report:
.B machinestate
.TP
Generate JSON report:
.B machinestate \-\-format json
.TP
Generate HTML report and save to file:
.B machinestate \-\-format html \-\-output report.html
.TP
Stream system data every 10 seconds:
.B machinestate \-\-stream \-\-interval 10
.TP
Stream specific collectors for 1 hour:
.B machinestate \-\-stream \-\-collectors system,disk \-\-duration 3600
.TP
Start HTTP server on port 8080:
.B machinestate \-\-http 8080
.TP
Run as MCP server for Claude Code:
.B machinestate \-\-mcp
.TP
Use custom config file:
.B machinestate \-\-config /path/to/config.yaml
.SH STREAMING OUTPUT
When using \fB\-\-stream\fR, output is JSONL (JSON Lines) with cycle markers:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{"_cycle":1,"_timestamp":"2025-12-30T10:00:00Z"}
{"collector":"system","timestamp":"...","data":{...}}
{"collector":"disk","timestamp":"...","data":{...}}
{"_cycle_complete":1}
{"_cycle":2,"_timestamp":"2025-12-30T10:00:05Z"}
...
{"_shutdown":true,"_total_cycles":10,"_timestamp":"..."}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Press Ctrl+C for graceful shutdown with shutdown marker.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, file write failure, server error)
